      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/45/36",
      "text": [
        " اِمْرَأَةٍ كَانَ لَهَا زَوْجٌ مَمْلُوكٌ فَوَرِثَتْهُ وَ أَعْتَقَتْهُ هَلْ يَكُونَانِ عَلَى نِكَاحِهِمَا قَالَ \"لاَ وَ لَكِنْ يُجَدِّدَانِ نِكَاحاً آخَرَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4652 - Abu al-Abbas and Ubayd narrated from Abu Abdullah (as) regarding a woman who had a slave husband, then inherited him and freed him. They asked if they would remain in their marriage.\nImam (as) said: \"No, but they must renew their marriage contract.\""
        ]
      }
